---

Bring a #large pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced). Trim ends from @zucchini{1}. Using a #peeler{}, shave zucchini lengthwise into thin ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core; discard core.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, remove sausage from casing; discard casing. Heat a dribble of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in garlic and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @marinara sauce{14%ounce cup} to pan with sausage mixture, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer until flavors meld and sauce is slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add spaghetti, ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) to pan with sauce. Toss to thoroughly combine. Separate zucchini ribbons with your hands, then stir into pasta until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until spaghetti is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide pasta between bowls; top with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and serve.